'''威尔弗里德·劳雷尔大学'''（Wilfrid Laurier University，又譯作[[偉佛羅利亞大學|偉佛羅利亞大學]]、[[勞里埃大學|勞里埃大學]]）是位于[[加拿大|加拿大]][[安大略|安大略]]省滑鐵盧市大學西街75號的一所公立大学，得名于[[加拿大历史|加拿大历史]]上第一位法裔[[加拿大总理|总理]][[威尔弗里德·劳雷尔|威尔弗里德·劳雷尔]]。 

该校在1911年時。名叫Evangelical Lutheran Seminary of Canada。1914年，改名Waterloo College School。1923年，再改名為Waterloo College of Arts。 1959年，又改名為University of Waterloo，後又改名Waterloo Lutheran University。1973年才改為現在的 Wilfrid Laurier University。

該大學是加拿大发展最快的大学之一，注册学生从1997年到2006年几乎翻倍。该校有三个校区，主校区位于安大略省[[滑鐵盧_(安大略省)|滑铁卢]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wlu.ca/homepage.php?grp_id=65 |title=Wilfrid Laurier University - Student Recruitment Office |access-date=2014-01-03 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304200755/http://www.wlu.ca/homepage.php?grp_id=65 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>在2014年[[麦克林|麦克林]]杂志的大学排名中，该校位居[[综合性大学|综合性大学]]（Comprehensive）的第十名。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://oncampus.macleans.ca/education/2013/10/31/2014-university-rankings-comprehensive-category-results/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101041516/http://oncampus.macleans.ca/education/2013/10/31/2014-university-rankings-comprehensive-category-results/ |archive-date=2014-01-01 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> <!--In 2013, Research Infosource Inc. ranked Laurier University in the top 50 of research universities in Canada, out of nearly 100 Canadian universities in existence.<ref>http://www.researchinfosource.com/pdf/2013Top50List.pdf</ref> Laurier is one of only 8 universities in Canada to have its own publishing company; it has a 39-year history.-->

==历史==
威尔弗里德·劳雷尔大學的历史溯源于1911的'''Waterloo Lutheran Seminary of Canada'''（加拿大滑铁卢[[路德宗|路德宗]]学院）， <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wlu.ca/~wwwsem/index.shtml |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2004-03-29 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040403170956/http://www.wlu.ca/~wwwsem/index.shtml |archivedate=2004-04-03 }}</ref> 
1914年，该学院发展了很多非[[神学|神学]]领域的课程被更名为 the Waterloo College School， 1924年更名为'''Waterloo College of Arts'''，并提供三年制的学士学位课程。 <ref name=autogenerated1>http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/index.cfm {{Wayback|url=http://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.com/index.cfm |date=20080726164759 }}? PgNm=TCE&Params=U1ARTU0003698</ref> 1925年，'''Waterloo College of Arts''' 成为[[西安大略大学|西安大略大学]]的附属学院。 

Laurier's school colours of purple and gold originated in 1927: maroon and gold were the colours of Waterloo College, but to honour the link with the University of Western Ontario, whose colours were purple and white, maroon was discarded in favour of purple.
[[File:LaurierU.jpg|thumb]] 

The Waterloo College Chapel features several stained glass windows including `Light of the world` (1941) and `Christ in the garden` (1940) by Robert McCausland Limited. 

[[滑铁卢大学|滑铁卢大学]]的歷史可追溯到1957年7月1日成立的[[滑鐵盧專科聯合學院|滑鐵盧專科聯合學院]](Waterloo College Associate Faculties)，是當時的[[滑鐵盧學院|滑鐵盧學院]]（即現在的[[威尔弗里德·劳雷尔大學|威尔弗里德·劳雷尔大學]]）的一個半自治部門機構。該機構於1959年正式脫離滑鐵盧學院並升格為大學。

1960年加拿大[[路德宗|路德宗]]教会结束了对[[滑鐵盧學院|滑鐵盧學院]]（Waterloo College）的资助，同时更名为'''Waterloo Lutheran University'''，同时该学院也不再是[[西安大略大学|西安大略大学]]的附属学院。 <ref name=autogenerated1 />

Wilfrid Laurier University was established by Wilfrid Laurier University Act 1973, which was amended in 2001.<ref>www.wlu.ca/page.php?grp_id=158&p=2235 Wilfrid Laurier University Act.</ref> 

<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Dscn0017.jpg|thumb]].]]  -->Laurier opened a second campus, in Brantford, Ontario, in 1999, and in 2006 the Lyle S. Hallman Faculty of Social Work moved from the Waterloo campus to a campus in downtown Kitchener. The Brantford campus is centred on a number of historic properties in the downtown area which have been restored for university use.  They include a former [[Carnegie_library|Carnegie library]], Brantford's 1880 post office, and 1870 mansion, and a 1950 Odeon Theatre. The Kitchener campus is located in the historic and fully renovated former St. Jerome's high school building.

In October 2008, the University was named one of [[Waterloo_Area's_Top_Employers|Waterloo Area's Top Employers]] and featured in the [[Waterloo_Region_Record|Waterloo Region Record]] and [[Guelph_Mercury|Guelph Mercury]] newspapers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eluta.ca/top-employer-wilfrid-laurier-university|title=Reasons for Selection, 2009 Waterloo Area's Top Employers Competition|access-date=2014-01-03|archive-date=2009-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090712032939/http://www.eluta.ca/top-employer-wilfrid-laurier-university|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[Waterloo_Lutheran_Seminary|Waterloo Lutheran Seminary]] continues to operate in affiliation with the University and the [[Evangelical_Lutheran_Church_in_Canada|Evangelical Lutheran Church in Canada]].

=== 校名 ===
滑鐵盧路德宗大學（Waterloo Lutheran University）在轉型為公立大學之時需要去除原校名中的宗教涵義。包括Beaver University、Riel University、the Iroquois University of Waterloo在內，一共有多達94個候選名稱。新校名最終於1973年被確定為威爾弗里德·勞雷爾大學（Wilfrid Laurier University）。有爭議的是彼時一些學生抗議稱Wilfrid Laurier實為一值得商榷的政治人物，且無論與學校還是滑鐵盧地區皆無任何聯繫。有猜測稱之所以命名為Wilfrid Laurier University是為了保留學校原有的首字母WLU，以減少更改檔案的麻煩。<ref>Cote, Kris: "The Cord History: The tie that's bound WLU for 80 years", page 13. Wilfrid Laurier University Student Publication, 2006.</ref>
<!--When [[Waterloo_Lutheran_University|Waterloo Lutheran University]] became a public university, a new name was needed. There were 94 proposed names, among them Beaver University, Louis Riel University and the Iroquois University of Waterloo. Eventually Wilfrid Laurier University was selected in 1973, but not without controversy, as some students at the time charged that [[Wilfrid_Laurier|Wilfrid Laurier]] was a politician of "questionable reputation" who had no connection to the school or the region of Waterloo. There has been speculation  over the years that the name Wilfrid Laurier University was chosen mainly to preserve the initials as WLU.<ref>Cote, Kris: "The Cord History: The tie that's bound WLU for 80 years", page 13. Wilfrid Laurier University Student Publication, 2006.</ref>-->

