== 学术 ==
The University is home to 14,116 full-time and part-time undergraduate students, 781 full-time and part-time graduate students and over 500 in faculty and staff,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wlu.ca/page.php?grp_id=12015&p=14901 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-01-03 |archive-date=2015-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514163703/http://www.wlu.ca/page.php?grp_id=12015&p=14901 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> although comparatively small, the university has consistently ranked among Canada's top schools in its category, an honour which is regularly confirmed by [[Maclean's|Maclean's]] magazine's annual rankings. The 2008 Macleans rankings placed Laurier fifth overall (first in Ontario) of the 21 Canadian universities in the category of "Primarily Undergraduate" universities.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.macleans.ca/education/rankings.jsp |title=存档副本 |access-date=2014-01-03 |archive-date=2008-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080221204043/http://www.macleans.ca/education/rankings.jsp |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

